@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{org-pomodoro-extras.el} extends @samp{org-pomodoro}, the Emacs implementation of the Pomodoro Technique integrated with Org mode task clocking. The standard @samp{org-pomodoro} package provides timers for work intervals (pomodoros) and breaks, but its modeline display and notification messages are not always ideal.

This package addresses two specific annoyances:

@itemize
@item
The default modeline format does not show how many pomodoros have been completed in the current session. The function @code{org-extras-pomodoro-format-timer} enriches the display with a pomodoro count (@ref{Timer formatting}).
@item
When a pomodoro is killed prematurely, the original notification includes a humorous but distracting message. A patch silences this in favor of a clean, empty notification body (@ref{Silencing the killed notification}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{el-patch} for modifying built-in behavior.

