@node Timer formatting
@section Timer formatting

@findex org-extras-pomodoro-format-timer
The function @code{org-extras-pomodoro-format-timer} updates the variable @code{org-pomodoro-format} to include both the remaining time and the current pomodoro count. The resulting modeline display looks like @samp{🍅 24:15|3}, where @samp{24:15} is the time remaining and @samp{3} is the number of pomodoros completed so far.

This function is intended to be called as advice on @code{org-pomodoro} itself, so that the count is refreshed each time a new pomodoro starts. Without this, the count shown in the modeline would be stale.

@node Silencing the killed notification
@section Silencing the killed notification

@findex org-pomodoro-killed
The function @code{org-pomodoro-killed} is patched via @samp{el-patch} to replace the original notification body (``One does not simply kill a pomodoro!'') with an empty string. The notification title (``Pomodoro killed.'') is preserved. All other behavior of the original function---resetting the timer, playing the killed sound, handling Org clock state, and running @code{org-pomodoro-killed-hook}---remains unchanged.

